        <h2>LEDs compare well against solar&nbsp;PV</h2>
        <p>Working on the assumption that a 49kW solar array generates 41,000kWh per year, costs £60,000 and lasts 20 years, its lifetime saving would be 820,000kWh or 338 tonnes of carbon. That’s about £180 per tonne of carbon (excluding the carbon cost of building the solar array).</p>
        <p>Based on our assumptions, a 100-house retrofit project would save 80,000kWh per year, cost £8,000 and last at least 5 years. The lifetime saving would be about 394,000kWh or 162 tonnes carbon, at a much lower cost of £49 per tonne.</p>
        <p>And that assumes that the LED light bulbs die exactly at the end of their 5 year warranty period. In reality, they may last 10 or 15 years.</p>
