      <h2>Light House is a Co-op service</h2>
      <p>Light House is a pilot project from the Co-op to make it simpler for community energy groups to deliver LED retrofitting.</p>
      <p>Community energy groups are excellent at raising community shares, engaging local people, and managing a community.</p>
      <p>However, community groups are likely to have difficulty administering large scale purchasing, delivery, management and customer service of a LED retrofitting scheme.</p>
      <p>The Co-op is a national organisation with a global reach. Through the Co-op, Light House can handle making large orders of bulbs on behalf of community groups, and deal with deliveries, warranties, returns and replacements.</p>
      <p>Light House combines the strength and network of community groups with the scale and digital capabilities of the Co-op.</p>

      <h2>The Light House service</h2>
      <p>Light House is a digital platform. The technical part of this is a bit like Ebay or Amazon, in that it connects people and manages the relationship between them. </p>
      <p>The Light House service connects community energy groups delivering LED refitting with households who want to switch to LED bulbs, and with the Co-op who make purchases and deliveries and handle replacements. The complex job of working out who needs what bulbs and how many is handled by the service, freeing up groups to focus on building relationships with households in their community.</p>

      <h2>How Light House works</h2>
      <p>The goal of Light House is to allow people who can’t afford the upfront cost of switching to LED bulbs to benefit from this energy saving technology and reduce their bills. </p>

      <ul>
        <li>community groups use their local knowledge and trust to recruit households who would benefit from the scheme</li>
        <li>community groups raise money for the bulbs through community shares</li>
        <li>households complete a one-off assessment of what bulbs they need, using the Light House service</li>
        <li>households pay a £1 per week subscription for 3 years.</li>
        <li>Light House handles orders, deliveries, returns and replacements</li>
        <li>community groups receive a dividend from Light House into their community benefit fund</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Light House makes it simple</h2>
      <p>Light House makes the delivery of LED retrofitting easy by automating these tasks</p>

      <ul>
        <li>data modelling for projects using number of houses, cost of installation, percentage interest and so on</li>
        <li>drafting community share offers based on the model parameters</li>
        <li>collecting information from households on what bulbs they require</li>
        <li>bulk purchasing and delivery of light bulbs to households</li>
        <li>collecting weekly payment from households and distributing back to the community energy company</li>
        <li>calculating interest payments to shareholders</li>
        <li>calculating figures for accounts</li>
        <li>managing warranty returns for any bulbs which break within warranty</li>
        <li>creating periodic reports on energy and carbon savings</li>
      </ul>

      <p>Community energy groups have done amazing things, and we think their journey can continue despite the government slashing feed-in tariffs. We want to support community groups to continue to lead the UK toward a better, low carbon future.</p>

